There are currently 5 different 'types' of guilds, although several types
have more than one guild within it's category.  The different types are:
DRUIDS, CLERICS, MAGES, THIEVES, and FIGHTERS.
 
Most classes have restrictions on what type of armours and which type of
weapons they are allowed to use.  When you design a piece of armour or
weapon, the type of armour or weapon and the material it's made of will
determine which guilds can use the weapon.  The following is a general
guildeline as to who can wear and use what:
 
CLASS       WEAPON TYPE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
MAGES      Daggers and staves.

THIEVES    Daggers, some blunt weapons (like a blackjack), medium size
            swords. No large weapons.

FIGHTERS   All, except for magic items that are guild specific.

DRUIDS     Daggers, blunt weapons, and most swords (except things like
           two-handed swords and such).

CLERICS    Blunt weapons only.
 
 
CLASS      ARMOUR TYPE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
MAGES      Only very light armours like robes, rings of protection, bracers
           of defense, etc.

THIEVES    Similar to mages, but not as strict.  Able to wear leather armour,

FIGHTERS   Anything, unless the item is guild specific.

DRUIDS     Similar to mages, except able to wear armours made from naturally
           growing materials, i.e. BarkMail.

CLERIC     Almost anything, unless it is a class specific item.
 
If you have any questions on what to set an object ask another wizard!
There are several examples in the /open/WEAPON and /open/ARMOUR
directories that show how to set guilds for weapons and armour.
 
Below is a complete listing of ALL guilds currently in the game and their
proper syntax when using them.
 
FIGHTER, GAROU, BARD, NECRO, DRUID, THIEF, MAGE, CHARLATAN
CLERIC_MITRA, MORPHER, LUNAR, PSIONICIST, SWASHBUCKLER, NINJA
 
ALL_GUILDS can be used when you wish to have something globally encompass
all guilds.

